subSubSection.paragraph:
Although there are some differences in the range of measurements of worms taken from hosts in different localities (see the table of comparative measurements in
Mawson 1960
) they appear to represent slight differences due to either the maturity of the worms, the effects of the host species and or the effects of differing fixation schedules rather than specific differences between populations.
